<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb9783d46-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3" identifier="/us/usc/t39/s5601"><num value="5601">§ 5601.</num><heading> Sea post service</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Postal Service may maintain sea post service on ocean vessels conveying mail to and from the United States.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb9783d47-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3">(<ref href="/us/pl/91/375">Pub. L. 91–375</ref>, <date date="1970-08-12">Aug. 12, 1970</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/84/773">84 Stat. 773</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
